commit_message:
Remove base_services_client for the reability

The service clients for the volume service are different from
the other services and it is a little difficult to read and
debug because that consists of multiple layers for v1 and v2.
That could be useful for the code optimization,  but actually
the merit seems small and unreadable.
This patch removes these layers from the volume clients.

Partially implements blueprint consistent-service-method-names

Change-Id: I06661fa4b0eb9ed961a4fd2cc9b89462ef45c271

commit_message:
Remove base_hosts_client for the reability

The service clients for the volume service are different from
the other services and it is a little difficult to read and
debug because that consists of multiple layers for v1 and v2.
That could be useful for the code optimization,  but actually
the merit seems small and unreadable.
This patch removes these layers from the volume clients.

Partially implements blueprint consistent-service-method-names

Change-Id: I176ca1fefcb93b1cc071ab02a53f89571d129b3f

commit_message:
Add Check for notification_driver

Adding check for notification_driver before sending messages to
notification queue. If notification_driver is available then
messages will be send to the queue otherwise the message is
logged.

Closes-Bug: #1452055

commit_message:
Add command to force a deploy failure

This can be used if a node gets stuck in a deploying state, as the
only option currently is to manually run a query in the database.
Operators should be able to run a script instead.

Run the command:
ironic-noderecover -h
ironic-noderecover --node_uuids=UUID1,UUID2  --config-file=/etc/ironic/ironic.conf

Partial-Bug: #1580931
Change-Id: I1256a81e26f16c8b450e65ee1b4524f47ae495cc

commit_message:
Remove ramdisk on unstack

Running devstack will not rebuild or replace the ramdisk if it already
exists. Remove it during unstack such that it is rebuilt or
re-downloaded during development, to avoid surprises.

Change-Id: Ifd29b3b8b583d9572358a85e6fa2a9f02ab092dc

commit_message:
Make port.save remotable

This makes the port.save() call remotable, and updates the API service
to use that method directly, rather than routing through an explicit RPC
method in the conductor.

Also deprecate the update_port conductor RPC call, as it's no longer
used. This should be removed in the next major RPC version.

In the spirit of live upgrades, we should be doing all writes (and
possibly reads?) in the conductor layer.

Change-Id: Ied2aa055d80d2a516f59001e560c97c743dcb0aa

commit_message:
Make port.destroy remotable

This makes the port.destroy() call remotable, and updates the API
service to use that method directly, rather than routing through an
explicit RPC method in the conductor.

Also deprecate the destroy_port conductor RPC call, as it's no longer
used. This should be removed in the next major RPC version.

In the spirit of live upgrades, we should be doing all writes (and
possibly reads?) in the conductor layer.

Change-Id: I91e509f6140a178df0a2283e7cd5d877712358ad

This makes the port.create() call remotable, which will cause the API
service to send the call over RPC to the conductor.

In the spirit of live upgrades, we should be doing all writes (and
possibly reads?) in the conductor layer.

Change-Id: I6607649460b235ed2fc9fcd1474c636271cb2a71

commit_message:
Clean up port API code

This cleans up a few hacks we have in the port API code to work around
the fact that we expose node_uuid to API clients, but only track node_id
in the Port object.

It also aims to reduce SQL queries in GET calls for ports, by joining
the node in the query rather than issuing a second query for it.

Change-Id: If9738e3671c1679332c3c1cecb87fe998f3339f2

This adds a 'node' attribute to the port object, allowing the node
object to be used directly from the port object, without explicitly
doing another query for it. A new ObjectField from oslo.versionedobjects
is added to support this.

The get(), get_by_id(), get_by_uuid(), get_by_address(), list(), and
list_by_node_id() methods on the Port class now all accept an optional
`expected_attrs` argument. This is a list of optional attributes from
objects.port.PORT_OPTIONAL_ATTRS to be eagerly loaded on the Port
object. The eager loading is done with a join in the database.
If the parameter is not passed, the node will be lazily loaded from the
DB on first use of the node attribute.

To support lazy loading, we define the obj_load_attr method on the Port
class, which is called from the o.vo base class when an attribute is
accessed that is not yet loaded on the object.

The _from_db_object now optionally loads the node object when requested.

The version for the Port object is bumped to 1.5 to signal this change
to RPC clients, and the hash in tests is updated accordingly.

A method obj_from_db_obj() is added to the Node object to allow
translating a node from the database into a Node object. The Node object
version is bumped to 1.15 to signal this.

The port objects tests are refactored, with coverage added for the
changes to the port object.

A hack (cribbed from Nova) is added to the object version hash test, to
look at a GENERATE_HASHES environment variable. If this variable is set,
the test will dump the version hashes into object_hashes.txt, allowing
developers to easily generate the new hashes when objects are changed.

Change-Id: Ibf933bcee54be876fd063131cd426ede6f1459a4

commit_message:
Attach related node to Port object

This adds a 'node' attribute to the port object, allowing the node
object to be used directly from the port object, without explicitly
doing another query for it. A new ObjectField from oslo.versionedobjects
is added to support this.

The get(), get_by_id(), get_by_uuid(), get_by_address(), list(), and
list_by_node_id() methods on the Port class now all accept an optional
`expected_attrs` argument. This is a list of optional attributes from
objects.port.PORT_OPTIONAL_ATTRS to be eagerly loaded on the Port
object. The eager loading is done with a join in the database.
If the parameter is not passed, the node will be lazily loaded from the
DB on first use of the node attribute.

To support lazy loading, we define the obj_load_attr method on the Port
class, which is called from the o.vo base class when an attribute is
accessed that is not yet loaded on the object.

The _from_db_object now optionally loads the node object when requested.

The version for the Port object is bumped to 1.5 to signal this change
to RPC clients, and the hash in tests is updated accordingly.

A method obj_from_db_obj() is added to the Node object to allow
translating a node from the database into a Node object. The Node object
version is bumped to 1.15 to signal this.

The port objects tests are refactored, with coverage added for the
changes to the port object.

A hack (cribbed from Nova) is added to the object version hash test, to
look at a GENERATE_HASHES environment variable. If this variable is set,
the test will dump the version hashes into object_hashes.txt, allowing
developers to easily generate the new hashes when objects are changed.

Change-Id: Ibf933bcee54be876fd063131cd426ede6f1459a4

commit_message:
Allow port to join nodes in the DB layer

This refactors some of the DB layer to allow the nodes table to be
joined to the port model. It:

* refactors the DB API to accept a list of columns to join to the SELECT
  queries for ports.

* adds the 'node' field to the port model as a FK relationship to the
  node table.

* tests all the things

If extra_attrs=['node'] is passed in to a method that selects ports
from the DB, the related node row will be eagerly joined in the query.

Change-Id: I92e6c8ac6b43b0c8744af3ed02d6105f3d9f8830

commit_message:
Make object methods remotable again

The remotable decorators were commented out when we landed the
indirection API code, because it was flaky and devstack. The change this
depends on should handle the flakiness by ensuring the conductor is
started before the API. Re-enable the remotable methods.

Change-Id: I2eba48b119ab72783d0d5290a8f22132df9d2efd

subject: go: make container timeout configurable
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-07-27 20:43:26.000000000', 'files': ['go/objectserver/main.go', 'go/hummingbird/conf_test.go', 'go/hummingbird/conf.go', 'go/objectserver/update.go'], 'message': "go: make container timeout configurable

Add 3 config options from the swift object server around timing out
container updates.

container_update_timeout sets how long it waits for a container
update before returning to the user and continuing the update
asynchronously.  This should just be set high enough that users
generally get a consistent view of containers.

conn_timeout sets how long it should wait for the TCP connect to
happen.

node_timeout sets how long it should give the request to succeed.

conn_timeout and node_timeout are defaulted to higher than swift's,
since container_update_timeout obviates the need for them to be
super aggressive.

Change-Id: I7220a909c1b92411e499fd00fcffd68be6733866
"}]
commit_message:
go: make container timeout configurable

Add 3 config options from the swift object server around timing out
container updates.

container_update_timeout sets how long it waits for a container
update before returning to the user and continuing the update
asynchronously.  This should just be set high enough that users
generally get a consistent view of containers.

conn_timeout sets how long it should wait for the TCP connect to
happen.

node_timeout sets how long it should give the request to succeed.

conn_timeout and node_timeout are defaulted to higher than swift's,
since container_update_timeout obviates the need for them to be
super aggressive.

Change-Id: I7220a909c1b92411e499fd00fcffd68be6733866

commit_message:
Use the most up-to-date lxc package when on 1404

This change updates the lxc package to use the lxc2 package
instead. This change will ensure we're getting a more updated
version of lxc on trusty than the standard package name provides
by default.

Change-Id: I283e2d3ce2c3441dd0f5f17163421fcf25988880
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Implement new heartbeat for AgentDeploy

Refactor heartbeat and related calls to a new AgentDeployMixin used
in AgentDeploy, ISCSIDeploy and BaseAgentVendor.

Also removes excessive passing of kwargs to where they are not used.
It has a potential of breaking out-of-tree drivers, but it also greatly
simplifies tracking how values are passed during deployment.

Also made several methods just functions.

Change-Id: I56c728c13b06f1aea0baeec0dddc7ba160a7a211
Partial-Bug: #1570841

commit_message:
go: set nodelay on repconn

Make sure repconn messages don't suffer nagle delays.
Use bigger buffers to make sure we make efficient use of packets.

I'd like to just use tcp_cork, but it's not exposed very well in go.

Change-Id: Id66c37eb877801706992ccc69d3801e0f7efd716

commit_message:
Add docs about microversion testing in Tempest

As discussed at the newton midcycle and in the dev
mailing list:

http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2016-July/099860.html

We should add a Tempest test for any microversion that
changes the response schema so we have coverage in Tempest
and also so we don't have to fill large gaps in coverage
in Tempest when adding other unrelated tests.

Change-Id: Ie7cfe7ee857caf630d4380cf673ae208842fbc00

The "delete volume on instance delete" option was being displayed

'}]
commit_message:
Remove duplicate 'delete volume' option  on launch instance

The "delete volume on instance delete" option was being displayed
twice when the boot source was volume or volume snapshots, and
once when the boot source was instance snapshot. This is because when
the option was being created for an image, the option was
duplicated onto every other source. This patch stops the option
from being replicated.

Closes-Bug: #1607976

Change-Id: I89f38041822e078bf4e0ceffebd33e2178c7a53e

commit_message:
Constraint to prevent duplicate endpoints

Prevent the creation of endpoints with duplicate combination of
service_id, region_id and interface by creating a unique constraint
in endpoint table.
Some tests that created duplicated entries were modified to comply
with this new constraint.
This patch also fixes the new_endpoint_ref helper method that didn't
include the 'enabled' attribute

Co-Authored-By: Henrique Truta <henrique@lsd.ufcg.edu.br>

Change-Id: I7bd44287953dc00d04396aeb18480c4d6aa6dc2d
Closes-Bug: #1376937

subject: Enable in-process func tests to optionally use encryption
revisions:
[{'number': 7, 'created': '2016-07-28 19:19:59.000000000', 'files': ['test/functional/__init__.py', 'doc/source/development_guidelines.rst', 'tox.ini'], 'message': 'Enable in-process func tests to optionally use encryption

Running functional tests in the in-process mode uses
the default value for the pipeline.  This patch adds support
to specify the SWIFT_TEST_IN_PROCESS_CONF_LOADER variable
to point to a labeled function that changes the proxy
configuration for the functional test.

The patch also adds a new tox environment
func-in-process-encryption
which runs with the environment variable
SWIFT_TEST_IN_PROCESS_CONF_LOADER=encryption

The motivation for this change is to put support in place for an
upstream CI job that will functionally test using encryption
middleware in the pipeline.  The gate job is proposed at:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/348292/

Change-Id: I15c4b20f1d2be57ae21c69c614f6a9579145bee9
'}]
commit_message:
Enable in-process func tests to optionally use encryption

Running functional tests in the in-process mode uses
the default value for the pipeline.  This patch adds support
to specify the SWIFT_TEST_IN_PROCESS_CONF_LOADER variable
to point to a labeled function that changes the proxy
configuration for the functional test.

The patch also adds a new tox environment
func-in-process-encryption
which runs with the environment variable
SWIFT_TEST_IN_PROCESS_CONF_LOADER=encryption

The motivation for this change is to put support in place for an
upstream CI job that will functionally test using encryption
middleware in the pipeline.  The gate job is proposed at:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/348292/

Change-Id: I15c4b20f1d2be57ae21c69c614f6a9579145bee9

commit_message:
Fix the provision playbook

There was a missing list item there, that causes the rebuild inventory
role to not get called. This caused issues with the rest of the
playbooks running as root on the virthost.

Change-Id: I152764b4c55ef7dbb9d71f0f37c08e9f904e2254

commit_message:
Initialise oslo.privsep early in main

Any process using oslo.privsep should now initialise the library before
first use with things like the rootwrap command to use.

This should be done near the top of main() in any command that expects
to make privileged calls via oslo.privsep (eg: cinder-volume, and not
cinder-api).

See I3ea73e16b07a870629e7d69e897f2524d7068ae8 for the corresponding
change in oslo.privsep.

Change-Id: Id9652ccf001a707fbd59e277c36817bd6d58e7b3
Closes-Bug: #1592043

revisions:

This provides an attribute which allows users to optionally disable using the
internal certs databag for SSL certificates. The use case is for people who are

certificates.

Change-Id: Ib7c578135db74675bd4c5a0da13f053f6474e0f1
'}]
commit_message:
Make certs databag optional

This provides an attribute which allows users to optionally disable using the
internal certs databag for SSL certificates. The use case is for people who are
using other external methods (such as the certificates cookbook) to manage
certificates.

Change-Id: Ib7c578135db74675bd4c5a0da13f053f6474e0f1

Add the languagepack delete functionality to the dashboard

The dashboard plugin currently does not support the option to delete a
selected languagepack. This patch adds this option to the dashboard
plugin.

Also, here is a link to a screenchot of what the page looks like before
confirming the delete: http://pasteboard.co/HU1vtWlb.png, and after
confirming the delete: http://pasteboard.co/HT6AoO5g.png

commit_message:
Add the languagepack show and log functionality to the dashboard

The dashboard plugin currently does not support the option to show the
details and logs for a selected languagepack. This patch adds this option
to the dashboard plugin.

Also, here is a link to a screenchot of what the page looks like:
http://pasteboard.co/HR1zlMgT.png

Closes-Bug: #1599566

commit_message:
Add the 'min' param to IntOpts where applicable

It was pointed out [0] that any IntOpt with a logical minimum value
should have that specified by including the 'min=' parameter in the
option definition. As that patch was concerned with the help text for
options, it was felt that a separate follow-up patch would be better for
adding these parameters.

[0] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/281901/7/nova/conf/network.py@259

Blueprint centralize-config-options-newton

Change-Id: I0dbef37736f72401268f3036f77f35a4bbf2b5b7

commit_message:
Mention proxy API deprecation microversion in api-ref

Proxy APIs are deprecated in microversion 2.36 which means
all proxy APIs will return 404 after 2.35 version.

It will be nice to mention that explicitly in api-ref too.

Partially implements blueprint deprecate-api-proxies

Change-Id: Iad210d215fb98bc247f049b23b97d8d7d4265c82

commit_message:
PCI-DSS Limit password changes per day

This patch limits the number of times a user can change their password
(self service) within a 24 hour period. This can be used to deter users
from changing their passwwords repeatedly in order to wipe out their
password history and reuse an old password.

Change-Id: Id84a4effd22a19a50f15572dd70b777321afad9b
Partially-implements: blueprint pci-dss

commit_message:
Make Dependency metadata optional

Currently X-Object-Meta-Storlet-Dependency is one of the required
metadata for storlet object file, but not all storlet applications
require dependencies.

This patch makes that metadata optional, and let us upload a storlet
object without adding an empty metadata to it.

Change-Id: I3514bd5447bab29dd906831d1d76c2b2f6851bd6

commit_message:
Fix updating allocation_pools on subnet update

Reference IPAM driver skipped subnet_update processing
if allocation_pools in subnet request are blank.

Built-in ipam implementation allows to update allocation pools
to blank value (i.e. clean up allocation pools for subnet).
To make Reference ipam driver consistent with built-in ipam
implementation allocation_pool check was removed.

Included UT to verify that allocation pools can be updated to blank
value now.

Change-Id: I0654e46d4bc60f6cf51ffddeead238dd4f064db2
Closes-Bug: #1605277

commit_message:
Set timeout value in urllib3.poolmanager.PoolManager

If timeout is not set in urllib3.poolmanager.PoolManager, it will
use "Python's default timeout for sockets", but if "timeout for
sockets" is not set, the timeout will be infinite(will not timeout).
so this is intented to set timeout value in urllib3.poolmanager.
PoolManager to avoid infinite timeout.

Change-Id: Ic035fdb93734c926b26b33feb610e0977e48c646
Closes-Bug: #1558931

CORS test now operates on test_resp instead of init_resp

Since send_init_request is now part of BTC, it no longer makes sense for the
CORS test to operate on init_request. Furthermore, the CORS test currently
throws an exception in master.

This change removes the return_netmask function, which was used to
provide an interface to the old inventory schema prior to Kilo. This is
no longer supported, so the function can be removed. The related
'old_netmask' variable was also deleted as it served no other purpose.

The 'old_address' variable was formerly constructed using either the
queue name (such as container or storage) that the IP address came from,
or with the name of the network interface. The queue name approach is
most recent, so the conditional for choosing between them was removed in
favor of simply using the queue name.

Also removed was a line for removing network address information from

commit_message:
Address low-hanging TODO items

This change removes the return_netmask function, which was used to
provide an interface to the old inventory schema prior to Kilo. This is
no longer supported, so the function can be removed. The related
'old_netmask' variable was also deleted as it served no other purpose.

The 'old_address' variable was formerly constructed using either the
queue name (such as container or storage) that the IP address came from,
or with the name of the network interface. The queue name approach is
most recent, so the conditional for choosing between them was removed in
favor of simply using the queue name.

Also removed was a line for removing network address information from
the top level of the host_var dictionary. This housekeeping is no longer
necessary.

Other TODOs remain, but this change was purposefully kept small as the
remaining changes are not as straightforward and may have broader
impact.

Change-Id: I5010107fdae077ff133e01c9369ddad28852637f

Merged barbican and key_manager conf files into one.

commit_message:
Replace functions 'Dict.get' and 'del' with 'Dict.pop'

Refactoring code: Making volume dict to use single instruction: pop()
rather than two instructions: get() and del, giving the codes a format
that carries through.

Change-Id: Ic889dac330eac24d15bd73186fc504402cddd861
Closes-Bug:#1571548

subject: Add 'vhdx' disk format.
revisions:
[{'number': 8, 'created': '2016-07-28 16:34:11.000000000', 'files': ['glance/common/config.py', 'etc/glance-api.conf', 'glance/contrib/plugins/image_artifact/v1/image.py', 'doc/source/glanceapi.rst', 'rally-jobs/plugins/plugin_sample.py', 'glance/tests/unit/v2/test_images_resource.py', 'releasenotes/notes/add-vhdx-format-2be99354ad320cca.yaml', 'doc/source/formats.rst'], 'message': "Add 'vhdx' disk format.

This patch adds the Hyper-V 'vhdx' disk format to the Glance
configuration. This allows users to upload 'vhdx' images by default.

'vhdx' disks can have much larger storage capacity than the older 'vhd'
format [1].  (Plus, anything with 'x' in the name is awesome.)

DocImpact: Docs will need to be updated to indicate that the 'vhdx'
disk_format is now one of the default disk formats supported by Glance.

UpgradeImpact: Adds 'vhdx' to the default list of disk_formats.  Operators
will no longer need to configure specifically to use 'vhdx' disks.

[1] https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/hh831446(v=ws.11).aspx

Spec-Lite: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/347626
Change-Id: I4e172c78d7afeb8be5a0123238efe3d8e4b044c9
"}]
commit_message:
Add 'vhdx' disk format.

This patch adds the Hyper-V 'vhdx' disk format to the Glance
configuration. This allows users to upload 'vhdx' images by default.

'vhdx' disks can have much larger storage capacity than the older 'vhd'
format [1].  (Plus, anything with 'x' in the name is awesome.)

DocImpact: Docs will need to be updated to indicate that the 'vhdx'
disk_format is now one of the default disk formats supported by Glance.

UpgradeImpact: Adds 'vhdx' to the default list of disk_formats.  Operators
will no longer need to configure specifically to use 'vhdx' disks.

[1] https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/hh831446(v=ws.11).aspx

Spec-Lite: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/347626
Change-Id: I4e172c78d7afeb8be5a0123238efe3d8e4b044c9

commit_message:
Bump minimum version of keystoneauth to 2.10

Keystoneauth 2.10 provides a few new features around authentication
plugins that will remove the need for some of the guessing
openstackclient does around things like when to prompt for password, and
more control over how auth plugins are created to let openstackclient
customize the process.

Change-Id: I5336315bc6a6ac97c32a9558f773b5535367358c

commit_message:
Use delorean-current for puppet modules

Currently we always build from source, but the latest master is now
available via delorean-current since o-p-m was broken into per-module
packages.

This should reduce the time taken to install everything from source,
and also provide a better path wnen upgrading as a simple
openstack undercloud install or yum update will update to the latest
puppet modules (currently failures happen if you forget to run via
tripleo.sh because the puppet modules aren't upgraded but things
that depend on the puppet modules are).

Also disable usage of the overcloud image cache as I have no idea what
will happen if we mix an image with puppet modules deployed from source
with ci scripts trying to install packaged modules.

Change-Id: Ie4cae6b884b2e539545371b9f716903b8fe5cf1f
Closes-Bug: #1597438

commit_message:
Fix for check_vlan_transparency on mech drivers not called

The check_vlan_transparency method on mech drivers is never
called by the neutron/plugins/ml2/managers.py MechanismManager
_check_vlan_transparency method since that method is invoked
before 'vlan_transparent' has been set in the context.
This fix moves the block in neutron/plugins/ml2/plugin.py
ML2Plugin._create_network_db to before the call to
'self.mechanism_manager.create_network_precommit(mech_context)'
so that vlan_transparent exists in the context when the
MechanismManager checks.

Change-Id: I8e47ccdebf0cb954109195e8a8ba39a1c82f97a8
Closes-Bug: #1602294

commit_message:
Replaces httplib with requests lib in Quobyte RPC layer

Simplifies the Manila Quobyte drivers rpc layer by using
requests library instead of httplib. This reduces overall
complexity and fixes randomly occurring rpc send issues.

Closes-Bug: #1560345

Change-Id: I4cc602722ece3761331bb3fa1c6bce2bbd35c78f

commit_message:
Block aggregate creation until main database empty

This makes Aggregate.create() fail until the main database has had all
of its aggreagtes migrated. Since we want to avoid any overlap or clashes
in integer ids we need to enforce this.

blueprint cells-aggregate-api-db

Change-Id: Iac04aa4d235a26fa4f6f2a49cefbce309668bdf9

commit_message:
Add SNI support via OS/python packages

To ensure that the Ansible venv has the right packages installed,
requirements.txt is updated with the appropriate packages.

To ensure that the OS for the deployment host is appropriately
prepared for the Ansible venv creation, to install pip, and
python packages into the venv, OS packages are installed.

Fedora install support is removed from the script as it is an
unsupported platform and unmaintained section.

Change-Id: Ib4e219294f5fd93c6a50814955ab97424a79dafd

Support to validate iLO SSL certificate in iLO drivers

support in iLO drivers to validate iLO SSL certificate.

Closes-Bug: #1599710

commit_message:
Fix get_server schema for v2.3

Since Icf6148017cdbc4f48d3ef9a964ee39fedda72b4e is merged,
testcases requiring v2.20 API started failing like that:
http://paste.openstack.org/show/527014/

To fix this, we add 'delete_on_termination' attribute to schema,
which is valid since v2.3 API.

There are also new extended server attributes when getting
server details, those are added here also. By default these
are only shown for an admin user and there aren't any existing
tests in Tempest which rely on this, but they are added here
for completeness.

Co-Authored-By: Matt Riedemann <mriedem@us.ibm.com>

Change-Id: I60161adf7e92c9013dd4bb1044e5ef0744e6e783
Closes-Bug: #1600186

commit_message:
Make certs databag optional

This provides an attribute which allows users to optionally disable using the
internal certs databag for SSL certificates. The use case is for people who are
using other external methods (such as the certificates cookbook) to manage
certificates.

Change-Id: Ib7c578135db74675bd4c5a0da13f053f6474e0f1

commit_message:
Enable keystone to use the SSL middleware

The http_proxy_to_wsgi middleware was recently added to keystone as
default in the pipeline [1]. So this takes it into use instead of the
non-standard option we were using before, which will be deprecated.

We already enable this middleware for nova, cinder and heat.

[1] Iad628a863e55cbf20c89ef23ebc7527ba8e1a835

Depends-On: I0fec98a6e1d9c8be4d8b8df382b78ba2815790f9

commit_message:
Add options to allow for selective git clone

This change adds to the ``$VAR_git_project_group: $NAME`` option
to the repo_packages files which will allow the py_pkgs plugin to
tag group association allowing us to selectively clone repositories
and build wheels based on services deployed.

Depends-On: I6a0508e8aaa4993bc68e72e3d2988d6db6470f6d
Change-Id: Id382219766c8a405c92f04d64bfb606db22abb8e
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Fix to solve None user id in existing_users context

This fix contains following changes
 - removed keystone version specific tenant_id fetch logic
 - called get_user_id api to fetch correct value of user_id
 - Updated Unittest case to cover modified code.

Change-Id: Id0c8135abe9d980b5a5f11e0123d7e9904c4f473
Closes-Bug: #1602157

commit_message:
Make NUMA topology filter consider resize flavor

This patch builds upon the FilterRequestSpec to leverage it to detect if
a new flavor was requested, and then calculate the NUMA topology from
the new flavor and use that for filtering.

Change-Id: Ib0d4df28382e2a1ee1ce3966f397903a97ad63df
Partial-bug: #1370390

commit_message:
NetApp: Refactor unit tests

Some of the older unit tests for the NetApp driver code
have become obsolete since adding new unit tests
over time. These tests also used mox in some places. So,

* Rewrite unit tests that were using mox
* Move unit tests to the right place in the test code tree
* Add unit tests and improve code coverage

Change-Id: I8c7bf93079bd67181994eb04487aff5575631153
Closes-Bug: #1514026

commit_message:
Remove unused Swift tempauth config

The tempauth middleware isn't used on the undercloud proxy server, in
fact it's not even included in the Swift proxy server pipeline
(see puppet-stack-config.yaml.template).

This patch basically removes the default tempauth configuration section
from the proxy server config.

Change-Id: I7e00d37a4f9c94826dbd58424707ff5fbb95b24c

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-07-31 04:06:17.000000000', 'files': ['cinderclient/v3/shell.py', 'cinderclient/v1/shell.py'], 'message': "print endpoints using new keystoneauth catalog object

cinderclient was assuming an identity v2 styled service catalog
would always be returned (when using `cinder endpoints`).

keystoneclient would return either a v2 or v3 styled catalog,
whereas keystoneauth abstracts out the differences and handles

Closes-Bug: 1608166
"}]
commit_message:
print endpoints using new keystoneauth catalog object

cinderclient was assuming an identity v2 styled service catalog
would always be returned (when using `cinder endpoints`).

keystoneclient would return either a v2 or v3 styled catalog,
whereas keystoneauth abstracts out the differences and handles
them internally. the result is that there is no need to look
for specific ['serviceCatalog'] or ['catalog'] keys in the
dictionary returned from keystoneauth.

it should be noted that perhaps cinderclient should deprecate
the ability to list endpoints since that is mostly an identity
and admin level operation, and likely an artifact from early
openstack days, it should now be handled by openstackclient.
further, it's not clear whether the command is meant to list all
endpoints or just the endpoints in the user's token (which it does
now).

Change-Id: Ibfcccedee5baf43f5b5c517d37e3f046c8743078
Closes-Bug: 1608166

subject: Increase the default max_overflow value
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-08-01 13:44:01.000000000', 'files': ['releasenotes/notes/increase-default-max-overflow-0af787268807f926.yaml', 'oslo_db/options.py'], 'message': 'Increase the default max_overflow value

It turned out that distribution of WSGI requests between forks is not
even when eventlet is used, which can cause pool timeout issues under
load, while there are idle workers with open DB connections, which
should have served these HTTP requests.

The default max_overflow value should be increased to allow DB oriented
services (mostly APIs) handle spikes in number of concurrent requests
trying to use a DB.

At the same time, the default number of greenlets is decreased:

 I65b40b9906b75146a0085bbe168f1e6bcae82f21

which effectively causes a particular worker to stop accepting new
requests it has no resources (DB connections) to handle and allow
other forks accept()'ing on the same FD to proceed.

Testing was performed using this script:

  https://gist.github.com/zzzeek/c69138fd0d0b3e553a1f

With 100 greenthreads in the pool, 50 DB connections allowed overflow
no pool timeout issues were seen with up to 500 concurrent requests
done by ab, while current default values (1000/10) could not handle
even 100 concurrent requests.

See this ML thread for details:

  http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-December/082717.html

DocImpact

This change potentially increases the number of connections open to the
RDBMS server. If you start seeing "too many connections" errors, please
check these settings and adjust them appropriately:

https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.5/en/server-system-variables.html#sysvar_max_connections
http://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/static/runtime-config-connection.html#GUC-MAX-CONNECTIONS

Closes-Bug: #1535375

Change-Id: I2e9c2a71d8231e0dfbefc6293ad319e1e459beec
(cherry picked from commit db5ecf69c8a13f96fbb00250a5fd3df312082b23)
'}]
commit_message:
Increase the default max_overflow value

It turned out that distribution of WSGI requests between forks is not
even when eventlet is used, which can cause pool timeout issues under
load, while there are idle workers with open DB connections, which
should have served these HTTP requests.

The default max_overflow value should be increased to allow DB oriented
services (mostly APIs) handle spikes in number of concurrent requests
trying to use a DB.

At the same time, the default number of greenlets is decreased:

 I65b40b9906b75146a0085bbe168f1e6bcae82f21

which effectively causes a particular worker to stop accepting new
requests it has no resources (DB connections) to handle and allow
other forks accept()'ing on the same FD to proceed.

Testing was performed using this script:

  https://gist.github.com/zzzeek/c69138fd0d0b3e553a1f

With 100 greenthreads in the pool, 50 DB connections allowed overflow
no pool timeout issues were seen with up to 500 concurrent requests
done by ab, while current default values (1000/10) could not handle
even 100 concurrent requests.

See this ML thread for details:

  http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-December/082717.html

DocImpact

This change potentially increases the number of connections open to the
RDBMS server. If you start seeing "too many connections" errors, please
check these settings and adjust them appropriately:

https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.5/en/server-system-variables.html#sysvar_max_connections
http://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/static/runtime-config-connection.html#GUC-MAX-CONNECTIONS

Closes-Bug: #1535375

Change-Id: I2e9c2a71d8231e0dfbefc6293ad319e1e459beec
(cherry picked from commit db5ecf69c8a13f96fbb00250a5fd3df312082b23)

commit_message:
Implement configurable start delay for containers

With the move of the container creation process from each service
playbook into the lxc-container-create playbook/role, it would be
appropriate to ensure that the delay implemented in the service
plays is implemented in the role.

This patch does so.

Change-Id: I473bcccde315ef66f45e912ad33ed665bed3b07c

subject: wsgi: decrease the default number of greenthreads in pool
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-08-01 13:39:09.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_service/_options.py'], 'message': "wsgi: decrease the default number of greenthreads in pool

It turned out that distribution of WSGI requests between forks is not
even when eventlet is used, which can cause pool timeout issues under
load, while there are idle workers with open DB connections, which
should have served these HTTP requests.

The default number of greenthreads in pool should be decreased to allow
DB oriented services (mostly APIs) distribute load more evenly between
workers: one worker will stop accepting new requests, when there are no
more available greenthreads in the wsgi pool, accept() will block, but
there are other forks accept()'ing on the same FD to handle connections
from the queue in kernel.

Related change to oslo.db:

  I2e9c2a71d8231e0dfbefc6293ad319e1e459beec

Testing was performed using this script:

  https://gist.github.com/zzzeek/c69138fd0d0b3e553a1f

With 100 greenthreads in the pool, 50 DB connections allowed overflow
no pool timeout issues were seen with up to 500 concurrent requests
done by ab, while current default values (1000/10) could not handle
even 100 concurrent requests.

See this ML thread for details:

  http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-December/082717.html

Closes-Bug: #1535375

Change-Id: I65b40b9906b75146a0085bbe168f1e6bcae82f21
(cherry picked from commit 321c185f3d977be153199a126720f6c3c00b0fdf)
"}]
commit_message:
wsgi: decrease the default number of greenthreads in pool

It turned out that distribution of WSGI requests between forks is not
even when eventlet is used, which can cause pool timeout issues under
load, while there are idle workers with open DB connections, which
should have served these HTTP requests.

The default number of greenthreads in pool should be decreased to allow
DB oriented services (mostly APIs) distribute load more evenly between
workers: one worker will stop accepting new requests, when there are no
more available greenthreads in the wsgi pool, accept() will block, but
there are other forks accept()'ing on the same FD to handle connections
from the queue in kernel.

Related change to oslo.db:

  I2e9c2a71d8231e0dfbefc6293ad319e1e459beec

Testing was performed using this script:

  https://gist.github.com/zzzeek/c69138fd0d0b3e553a1f

With 100 greenthreads in the pool, 50 DB connections allowed overflow
no pool timeout issues were seen with up to 500 concurrent requests
done by ab, while current default values (1000/10) could not handle
even 100 concurrent requests.

See this ML thread for details:

  http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-December/082717.html

Closes-Bug: #1535375

Change-Id: I65b40b9906b75146a0085bbe168f1e6bcae82f21
(cherry picked from commit 321c185f3d977be153199a126720f6c3c00b0fdf)

them.

* cloudkitty-dashboard
* murano-agent
* nova-docker
* os-net-config

commit_message:
Add backup update function (microversion)

Add update interface so that users can update
name and description of a backup.

This new API endpoint is added in microversion 3.9.

APIImpact
Add PUT to /backups/<id>.

DocImpact

Change-Id: If592b53c7e1dcdc36dbcaa89425b8e44a51684c3

subject: Use constraints for venv
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-07-29 07:16:24.000000000', 'files': ['jenkins/jobs/openstack-publish-jobs.yaml', 'jenkins/jobs/python-jobs.yaml'], 'message': 'Use constraints for venv

Use zuul-cloner with constraints for python jobs that use venv.
Those jobs all run on ubuntu nodes, so zuul-cloner is available.

Note that we can switch using constraints in projects yet since the
translation jobs use venv environment and run on the proposal node that
does not have constraints setup.

Change-Id: I1cd03efc184a7fba6073afd0dd16e6e9f17facd8
'}]
commit_message:
Use constraints for venv

Use zuul-cloner with constraints for python jobs that use venv.
Those jobs all run on ubuntu nodes, so zuul-cloner is available.

Note that we can switch using constraints in projects yet since the
translation jobs use venv environment and run on the proposal node that
does not have constraints setup.

Change-Id: I1cd03efc184a7fba6073afd0dd16e6e9f17facd8

commit_message:
Ensure IRONIC_BUILD_DEPLOY_RAMDISK is always explict

This patch ensures that we are always explictly setting the
IRONIC_BUILD_DEPLOY_RAMDISK option in the Ironic jobs, so that the
defaults defined by the Ironic devstack plugin don't affect the way the
job runs.

Closes-Bug: #1607981
Change-Id: I33361a48273fa82b9d7ce82ca67b22642af04f68

commit_message:
Standalone strategy "auth_strategy=none" not suitable for mitaka release

When Using Bare Metal service as a standalone service,
to disable the usage of identity service tokens the default
auth_strategy should be set 'noauth' for mitaka release

Change-Id: Ibd4037ba82b4c4074fbf284345f39a44219b0a5a
Closes-Bug: #1603368

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-07-29 18:24:42.000000000', 'files': ['trove_dashboard/content/databases/tests.py', 'trove_dashboard/api/trove.py', 'trove_dashboard/test/settings.py', 'tox.ini'], 'message': 'Fix gate test failures

The horizon settings have changed and the corresponding changes
were not picked up the trove-dashboard.  Import the horizon settings
file to prevent code skew and add the panels to the list of
installed apps.

Once the above was fixed it revealed one code change that was
needed due to commit ea0e472edd194243392fd51a5af3a3a77101fddd.
The Paginated object was changed in the above commit resulting
in the change in the trove.py file.  Also changed the test to

Change-Id: Id484fe373b79f00b90ca8b890aa3b9f73a475a50
'}]
commit_message:
Fix gate test failures

The horizon settings have changed and the corresponding changes
were not picked up the trove-dashboard.  Import the horizon settings
file to prevent code skew and add the panels to the list of
installed apps.

Once the above was fixed it revealed one code change that was
needed due to commit ea0e472edd194243392fd51a5af3a3a77101fddd.
The Paginated object was changed in the above commit resulting
in the change in the trove.py file.  Also changed the test to
reflect the new signature.

Also changed the tox.ini to be consistent with the horizon tox.ini.

commit_message:
Action status updating tag changed from 201 to 200

According to networking API v2.0 extensions, when tags
are added to resources, they use the REST "PUT" method. Being that
the resource is being modified and not created, and the PUT method
is used, both the update and update_all action_statuses should be
200. The API does not specify the normal response code for these
actions specifically, but it is assumed to be 200.

Change-Id: I2d48e586ed3583d053876f94daf9439225d3d41b
Closes-bug: #1606659

commit_message:
Do not override credential provider in tenant isolation tests

Currently the dynamic cred provider will be overrided each time
when the dynamic crededentials were generated. It causes resource
leakage in tests which used multiple dynamic credentials
e.g tenant isolation tests.

This patch makes cred generator reuse dynamic cred provider which
used for creation of first isolated credentials for second isolated
credentials too.

Change-Id: I657d66fd7cc4463e6a97cbf25d3db0cd6ff66602
Closes-Bug: #1606987

commit_message:
SoftwareComponent implementation

Added two classed to implement two basic application workflows:
installation and software configuration, with appropriate error
handling, reporting, event-based notifications and so on. A class
called 'SoftwareComponent' inherits both these classes and is able to
run these two workflows sequentially to install and configure software
on given Instance Groups.

Change-Id: Ic0c1bbad1f0e3ae71b339c56db245075bcc420ac
Targets-blueprint: application-development-framework

commit_message:
Add the languagepack list functionality to the dashboard

The dashboard plugin currently does not support languagepack
functionalities. The patch adds support to the plugin for listing
languagepacks.

To test the patch, download the patch, and replace the changed files in
the /opt/stack/solum-dashboard directory in the devstack setup.

Also, here is a link to a screenchot of what the page looks like:
http://pasteboard.co/HYOOPBgO.png

Closes-Bug: #1597373

commit_message:
Check object metadata constraints after authorizing

In the object proxy controller, the POST method checked the metadata of an
object before calling swift.authorize. This could allow an auth middleware to
set metadata that violates constraints. Instead, checking the metadata should
take place after authorization.

Change-Id: I5f05039498c406473952e78c6a40ec11e8b53f8e
Closes-Bug: #1596944

commit_message:
Use context.from_dict to determine available arguments

RequestContext.__init__ takes and ignores arbitrary keyword arguments.
This leads to mistakes such as those changed in tests and will prevent
cinder from passing those keyword arguments to the base oslo_context
class.

The ignored arguments are generally made up of things that oslo_context
added to the to_dict that cinder doesn't handle. Instead of accepting
and ignoring those arguments make from_dict smart enough to construct
the correct arguments to the class.

Related-Bug: #1602081
Change-Id: Iaf37e38ddc368a6f504bab17163d7f0ba21f5029

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-08-01 11:28:31.000000000', 'files': ['src/lib/charm/openstack/designate.py', 'unit_tests/test_designate_handlers.py', 'src/templates/novarc', 'unit_tests/test_lib_charm_openstack_designate.py', 'src/reactive/designate_handlers.py'], 'message': 'Make domain config mutable

Previously domain config has been immutable. Meaning that it could
be amended or set for the first time post deployment. This change
fixes that. In the process some other enhancements were made.

* Create and use check_zone_ids contextmanager to detect if domain
  ids have changed. If they have then update peers via leadership db.
* Rendering all configs is now a two stage process.
  render_base_config is called first to ensure that the Designate API
  servce is up and configured as the sink configs query the designate
  API to retrieve the domain ids for the neutron and nova domains.

  of handlers and stop gating on domains.created which previously

Change-Id: I477ad22bf9131672f6521d6afbf6f16a01d8b112

commit_message:
Make domain config mutable

Previously domain config has been immutable. Meaning that it could
be amended or set for the first time post deployment. This change
fixes that. In the process some other enhancements were made.

* Create and use check_zone_ids contextmanager to detect if domain
  ids have changed. If they have then update peers via leadership db.
* Rendering all configs is now a two stage process.
  render_base_config is called first to ensure that the Designate API
  servce is up and configured as the sink configs query the designate
  API to retrieve the domain ids for the neutron and nova domains.
* designate_handlers.py has been simplified to reduce the number
  of handlers and stop gating on domains.created which previously
  made domain config options immutable.
* templates/novarc was hard coded to use http. this has been updated
  to set the protocol based on whats passed back from keystone.

Change-Id: I477ad22bf9131672f6521d6afbf6f16a01d8b112

commit_message:
Use self.ks_logger instead of ks_logger

Currently with '--debug' option any cinder command only logs the
request from keystoneauth and not the main cinder service request.

Added keystoneauth logger to self.ks_logger so that logs can be
logged as expected.

Closes-Bug: #1606814

Change-Id: I7193aa6f43cb3186c49fc409b6e1ce7a36f596f9

If some sequence of commands is executed from tests using SSHClient
instance for each execution, there can be wrong expectation that
the previous command can change the current directory, and the next
command can be executed within the changed directory.
Actually, each invocation of SSHClient instance change the current

'}]
commit_message:
Extend _ManageSSH docstring with a note for current directory

If some sequence of commands is executed from tests using SSHClient
instance for each execution, there can be wrong expectation that
the previous command can change the current directory, and the next
command can be executed within the changed directory.
Actually, each invocation of SSHClient instance change the current
directory to the root of current user home directory.

- add a note to _ManageSSH docstring about the SSHClient behaviour.

Change-Id: I2585c68ada685460c4254c2728482961b3878753

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-06-28 04:00:45.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/unit/compute/test_compute_api.py', 'nova/compute/api.py'], 'message': 'Perform local delete for VMs in error

Right now, we will short-circuit early and not even do a full
local_delete() from the api because instance.host is not set. This
patch makes us not short circuit when instances are in error state as
they may have been through any number of build attempts and have (by
definition) made it further through the process than that short
circuit path expects. Calling local_delete() makes sure we clean up
any resources that may have been allocated for the instance, like
neutron ports.

Change-Id: I9faafab808f4dce593f7373d149a32bdac319bfa
Closes-Bug: #1594604
'}]
commit_message:
Perform local delete for VMs in error

Right now, we will short-circuit early and not even do a full
local_delete() from the api because instance.host is not set. This
patch makes us not short circuit when instances are in error state as
they may have been through any number of build attempts and have (by
definition) made it further through the process than that short
circuit path expects. Calling local_delete() makes sure we clean up
any resources that may have been allocated for the instance, like
neutron ports.

Change-Id: I9faafab808f4dce593f7373d149a32bdac319bfa
Closes-Bug: #1594604

commit_message:
Fixing jenkins failing on coverage reporting

Coverage combine deletes reports and thus jenkins failed
saying `no data to report`, this change fixes it.

Change-Id: Ia95ec755513d4382f9ad945e9688836445aee4d3

revisions:
[{'number': 20, 'created': '2016-07-29 21:17:49.000000000', 'files': ['scripts/common_functions.sh', 'scripts/deploy.sh', 'toci_gate_test.sh'], 'message': "Test overcloud deletion in periodic job

Recently I've seen a number of breakages where Heat can't delete a
stack that was deployed with network isolation enabled.  To avoid
promoting a repo with a broken Heat, we should test it in the
periodic job.

I'm not adding it to any of the regular jobs because the stack
deletion takes a significant amount of time (3.5 minutes in one
job I checked) and the main thing I'm concerned with is not
promoting a broken Heat.

Change-Id: I23ff8e9b2cc3676957a13d7efc42831693a97afe
"}]
commit_message:
Test overcloud deletion in periodic job

Recently I've seen a number of breakages where Heat can't delete a
stack that was deployed with network isolation enabled.  To avoid
promoting a repo with a broken Heat, we should test it in the
periodic job.

I'm not adding it to any of the regular jobs because the stack
deletion takes a significant amount of time (3.5 minutes in one
job I checked) and the main thing I'm concerned with is not
promoting a broken Heat.

Change-Id: I23ff8e9b2cc3676957a13d7efc42831693a97afe

commit_message:
[Verify] New command to list Tempest plugins

This command allows us to list all Tempest plugins.

E.g.
  $ rally verify listplugins
+----------------------------+--------------------------------------------+
|            Name            |                 EntryPoint                 |
+----------------------------+--------------------------------------------+
| hello-world-tempest-plugin | hello_world_tempest_plugin.plugin:MyPlugin |
+----------------------------+--------------------------------------------+

Change-Id: Ifd53afd749ac47893b0fa11168b30d2536bf89fa

commit_message:
Add initial framing of placement API

The placement API will initially host resource provider
information and then will grow to provide a full placement
service. Eventually it will be fully extracted from Nova.

To facilitate that extraction, this service is being developed
with few ties to existing nova.wsgi structures. Instead it
uses relatively plain WSGI apps that are:

* uses the Routes library with declarative mapping defined in
  ROUTE_DECLARATIONS
* basic wsgi apps, with webob and the request class, for each handler
  define as functions
* does not use a paste-ini file to compose middleware, instead code
  which minimally inspects the oslo config to know how to adjust
  middleware (in the initial case choosing an auth_strategy)

Many of these "features" will be demonstrated in commits that
follow this one that enable specific behaviors for resource
providers and their inventories.

In order to ensure that this change can be merged in an atomic
fashion it includes microversion support that was previously in its
own commit.

The microversion_parse library is used in a WSGI middleware
to parse incoming microversion headers and place the
determined value into the WSGI environment at the
'placement.microversion' key. Response headers are adjusted to
add the required outgoing headers as described in:

http://specs.openstack.org/openstack/api-wg/guidelines/microversion_specification.html

If a client requests an invalid microversion, they will receive
a 400 response. If the microversion is of a valid form but not
available, they will received a 406 response. The format of that
response is dependent on the accept header of the request. If it
is JSON, the min and max available microversions are presented.

A request to '/' will return version discovery information.

Thus far nothing else is done with the microversion information.
It is there for when we need it in the future. For now everything
is version 1.0.

The groundwork for using gabbi to test the API is in place in
nova/tests/functional/api/openstack/placement. The gabbi tests
are included in the functional target. To run just the placement
tests it is possible to run 'tox -efunctional placement'.

Change-Id: Icb9c8f7a1fa8a9eac66c2d72f4b7e4efd4e1944f
Partially-Implements: blueprint generic-resource-pools

commit_message:
Exit process without exiting interactive python interpreter

sys.exit() calls in main() will make the interactive
python interpreter exit. Using sys.exit(main()) can get more info
from the interpreter(prints the exit code and doesn't need to check
exit code in Shell with "$?") and retain the interpreter.

Change-Id: Ie6c4e039140039997b909810c61427afa4308963

commit_message:
Use assert(Not)In/Less/GreaterEqual/Equal

Instead of using assertTrue(A * B) / assertFalse(A * B)
developers should use assertNotIn, assertIn, assertLess,
GreaterEqual or assertEqual

Change-Id: Ifd336b0ef4dd970fe36028b20c8eee465efa4c84

commit_message:
Fix API Tests

Currently, when we run api tests with command: "tox -e api",
tests are failing with errors.

This change first fixes errors, make api tests pass. Then refactor
the neutron-vpnaas api tests tree to fit the tempest plugin.

As a tempest plugin, the steps to run tests by hands are:

1. Setup a local working environment for running tempest
    tempest init ${your_tempest_dir}

2. Enter ${your_tempest_dir}
    cd ${your_tempest_dir}

3. Check neutron_vpnaas_tests exist in tempest plugins:
    tempest list-plugins
    +----------------------+------------------------------------------------------+
    |         Name         |                      EntryPoint                      |
    +----------------------+------------------------------------------------------+
    |    neutron_tests     |  neutron.tests.tempest.plugin:NeutronTempestPlugin   |
    | neutron_vpnaas_tests | neutron_vpnaas.tests.tempest.plugin:VPNTempestPlugin |
    +----------------------+------------------------------------------------------+

4. Run neutron_vpnaas tests:
    tempest run --regex "^neutron_vpnaas.tests.tempest.api\."

In the jenkins gate,  devstack-gate/devstack-vm-gate-wrap.sh will invoke tempest
with proper configurations, such as:
    DEVSTACK_GATE_TEMPEST=1
    DEVSTACK_GATE_TEMPEST_ALL_PLUGINS=1
    DEVSTACK_GATE_TEMPEST_REGEX="^neutron_vpnaas.tests.tempest.api\."
The actual raw command in gate running under the tempest code directory is:
    tox -eall-plugin -- "^neutron_vpnaas.tests.tempest.api\."

commit_message:
ScaleIO to get volume name from connection properties

Currently ScaleIO is doing a HTTP request to find out what is the
volume id. This change will take it from the connection properties.
It is more accurate and saves time.

commit_message:
Compound alarm expression

Commits provides ability to specify alarm
expressions composed of multiple sub-expressions.

Following features/changes are made:
* responsive UI based on browser window size
* rewrite expression widget to act as
full-featured Angular directive
* directive submits compiled expression into
hidden input
* any error in any of sub expressions form
results in clearing the expression value and
effectively prevents user from reaching next
step
* sub-expressions can be:
** added
** removed
** reorganized

Change-Id: I1b4bd51e8887bc44dd3e2ffab4900d29fc77b77e

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-07-29 19:06:55.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/drivers/solidfire.py', 'cinder/tests/unit/test_solidfire.py'], 'message': "Add lock decorator to SolidFire clone_image method

When using the SolidFire template-caching feature, if a
template volume doesn't exist and multiple calls are made
at the same time to create a volume from image, we can run
in to a couple of problems.

1. It's possible to clone the template volume before the
   image conversion is actually completed (so the clone is
   a corrupt volume).
2. Hit a race where a subsequent call doesn't get the in
   progress template create and creates a duplicate.

We can fix this by using a lock decorator around the
clone_image method in the driver.

Change-Id: I0000c5bf29629fc1ded7b9e3ae26989fbf9dc286
Closes-Bug: #1605027
(cherry picked from commit 0273dc5b6d4e95ab3d1c945378637221cd421989)
"}]
commit_message:
Add lock decorator to SolidFire clone_image method

When using the SolidFire template-caching feature, if a
template volume doesn't exist and multiple calls are made
at the same time to create a volume from image, we can run
in to a couple of problems.

1. It's possible to clone the template volume before the
   image conversion is actually completed (so the clone is
   a corrupt volume).
2. Hit a race where a subsequent call doesn't get the in
   progress template create and creates a duplicate.

We can fix this by using a lock decorator around the
clone_image method in the driver.

Change-Id: I0000c5bf29629fc1ded7b9e3ae26989fbf9dc286
Closes-Bug: #1605027
(cherry picked from commit 0273dc5b6d4e95ab3d1c945378637221cd421989)

use tooz to track all metricd agents. grab a block based on number

commit_message:
add support for coordination

use tooz to track all metricd agents. grab a block based on number
of agents active. block size is based on the largest agent with
the largest number of workers

if coordination fails or is not supported, by default, all agents
work against same block with block size based on workers of each
agent.

Change-Id: I291b30f896f5e538040bf8f64d879eb1ad949395

commit_message:
Add user trust manager

As we know, operation may happen at any time. we should have a
correct token of Keystone to send quests when the operation is
triggered. When creating a new scheduled operation, create a
'trust' in Keystone, and then we can generate valid token by it.

Change-Id: I16217f37548ba501c7ca6b9ac6f220076afe0072
Closes-Bug: #1604244

subject: Fix COPY request
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-08-01 08:48:39.000000000', 'files': ['Engine/swift/storlet_middleware/handlers/proxy.py', 'install/storlets/roles/common_files/swift_config.py'], 'message': 'Fix COPY request

Currently COPY middleware is created in swift, and
"COPY" is allocated to the left of the "storlets_handler"
in the pipeline of proxy-server.
Therefore COPY request is processed in the COPY middleware.

In this case , there is the following problem.
1. Failed content_length check
 Because storlets doesn't set content_length.
2. COPY request handles storlets twice
 storlets is processed in the GET request and the PUT request.

This patch moves storlet_handler to the left of
copy middleware, to process COPY request in storlet_handler,
as we did with previous swift.

Change-Id: I325e28451bf0ee1dead88e0cb6009d3f7265b677
Closes-Bug: #1606446
'}]
commit_message:
Fix COPY request

Currently COPY middleware is created in swift, and
"COPY" is allocated to the left of the "storlets_handler"
in the pipeline of proxy-server.
Therefore COPY request is processed in the COPY middleware.

In this case , there is the following problem.
1. Failed content_length check
 Because storlets doesn't set content_length.
2. COPY request handles storlets twice
 storlets is processed in the GET request and the PUT request.

This patch moves storlet_handler to the left of
copy middleware, to process COPY request in storlet_handler,
as we did with previous swift.

Change-Id: I325e28451bf0ee1dead88e0cb6009d3f7265b677
Closes-Bug: #1606446

commit_message:
command in doc is incorrect

When following the doc instruction I found some command is incorrect
Like: --desired-capacity <desired-capacity>
Since newer version of python-client will use --os-profile instead of
--profile, now the command with --profile is in confliction. Maybe we
should use 'senlin' for now. And change it when python-client is
ready in April 2017. In this way, the new user or contributer in
senlin will have a clear tutorial.

Change-Id: If442f78f60d6cbbc5e8f35e8e617f917a7a16efe

commit_message:
Move the HA setup notes to its own page

This moves the guide on setting up high availability from the easily
missed note under Basic deployment to its own page under Advanced
deployment.

HA is an advanced mode of deployment -- one that requires the operators
to learn Pacemaker, deal with more complex configuration of services,
etc.

The page can later be augmented with notes on debugging a HA setup and
talk about pacemaker-lite once that's ready.

Change-Id: If10f00ddebe52d9d19d8c2a1e3b8394115852d60

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-05-24 09:43:21.000000000', 'files': ['nailgun/nailgun/objects/node.py', 'nailgun/nailgun/test/integration/test_node_handler.py'], 'message': "Accept interfaces changes only in discovery/error

By our design we accept changes to node interfaces only if node in
DISCOVERY and ERROR states. There are few reasons why we're doing so,
including one that IP addresses are assigned to bridges, not to NICs
and we ignore it in order to be able to redeploy nodes.

However, there's one case when node status is *artificially* changing
to ERROR state, implicitly allowing to accept interfaces changes. The
case is:

* Admin (PXE) interface is down on a node.
* nailgun-agent sends wrong node's IP address that will be used to
  check whether it belongs to Admin (PXE) network or not.
* If it doesn't belong, change node status to ERROR.
* Since the status is ERROR, changes to interfaces are allowed.
* Move admin network to another interface, which is wrong since
  physical connection wasn't changed.

to Admin (PXE) network is allowed.

Change-Id: I17e87e27d846921d6f0da535b9446e716449db95
Closes-Bug: #1532823
(cherry picked from commit 5925c52524cf4b1a540c021d96ef3e521bc71228)
"}]
commit_message:
Accept interfaces changes only in discovery/error

By our design we accept changes to node interfaces only if node in
DISCOVERY and ERROR states. There are few reasons why we're doing so,
including one that IP addresses are assigned to bridges, not to NICs
and we ignore it in order to be able to redeploy nodes.

However, there's one case when node status is *artificially* changing
to ERROR state, implicitly allowing to accept interfaces changes. The
case is:

* Admin (PXE) interface is down on a node.
* nailgun-agent sends wrong node's IP address that will be used to
  check whether it belongs to Admin (PXE) network or not.
* If it doesn't belong, change node status to ERROR.
* Since the status is ERROR, changes to interfaces are allowed.
* Move admin network to another interface, which is wrong since
  physical connection wasn't changed.

The commit introduces additional condition when the check for belonging
to Admin (PXE) network is allowed.

Change-Id: I17e87e27d846921d6f0da535b9446e716449db95
Closes-Bug: #1532823
(cherry picked from commit 5925c52524cf4b1a540c021d96ef3e521bc71228)

3) The example DNS server duplicated the example public VIP from

commit_message:
Update overcloud SSL docs

A few issues have been found with the current docs:
1) Something* has changed with the way we allocate VIPs that causes
   the previously documented method of predicting the public VIP to
   not work correctly.  This is addressed by explicitly setting the
   public VIP with PublicVirtualFixedIPs, which better matches what
   we do in CI anyway.
2) The indentation of the sample SSLCertificate entry was wrong.
   It has now been fixed.
3) The example DNS server duplicated the example public VIP from
   earlier in the doc.  To avoid confusion, that has been changed.

*: Likely I52e4485e832cbe6798de6b4afb6a7cfd88db11e2 in Neutron.

Change-Id: Id81896fb5943c160412c49355d3d85f0ded3b0fb

commit_message:
Update heat-agents setup files

This patch moves the image pull step out of the service heat-agent
service script to ease the service init process and to make it more
reliable. By doing this outside of the service script, it's possible to
know when the `firstboot` script failed and report back.

It also updates the firstboot yaml file to point to the
`tripleoupstream` org.

Co-Authored-By: Flavio Percoco <flavio@redhat.com>
Co-Authored-By: Martin André <m.andre@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I2f0b8092ec69320ee370e1d7d20b8c15c95a1d0d

subject: Fix network-isolation.yaml to stop clobbering Management net
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-07-12 19:20:39.000000000', 'files': ['environments/network-isolation.yaml'], 'message': "Fix network-isolation.yaml to stop clobbering Management net

The network-isolation.yaml file explicitly set the Management
network to None and the ports to noop.yaml. This resulted in the
Management network being disabled if network-management.yaml was
included before network-isolation.yaml.

These changes comment out the Management declarations to show the
default, and mention that network-management.yaml may be included.
Since the Management network is disabled by default, it isn't
necessary to noop it here. This change also places the Redis VIP
in a more logical place next to the controller ports.

Change-Id: I50a71b3ddf77bda2d213821da5e4260b503a6cb7
Fixes-bug: 1602283
(cherry picked from commit bf41f8f358fc2ae7dde1f7be94aa9027a27db09d)
"}]
commit_message:
Fix network-isolation.yaml to stop clobbering Management net

The network-isolation.yaml file explicitly set the Management
network to None and the ports to noop.yaml. This resulted in the
Management network being disabled if network-management.yaml was
included before network-isolation.yaml.

These changes comment out the Management declarations to show the
default, and mention that network-management.yaml may be included.
Since the Management network is disabled by default, it isn't
necessary to noop it here. This change also places the Redis VIP
in a more logical place next to the controller ports.

Change-Id: I50a71b3ddf77bda2d213821da5e4260b503a6cb7
Fixes-bug: 1602283
(cherry picked from commit bf41f8f358fc2ae7dde1f7be94aa9027a27db09d)

commit_message:
Allow for retries after certain resource delete failures

In cases where a resource is "in use," a Conflict exception may be
thrown, in which case it is worth trying to delete again up to
action_retry_limit times before giving up. Also introduce the
exception PhysicalResourceExists for future use.

Change-Id: Ib9305ff55904638491c6d43599a639d3a658f54b

commit_message:
Don't overwrite ceph osd_journal_size

The default journal size is 5 gigs. This change stops us
overwriting it with 1 gig that is too small for production.

The config value is used by ceph only when it creates the
journal so this does not affect upgrades.

Closes-Bug: 1589909

Change-Id: I4bfd2ab47e131d8fcdd5dc75a5a56cfae8b22d5a
(cherry picked from commit 815ef9958d67e00925f13c5d23fc3898da9588e1)

commit_message:
IPMITool: add IPMISocatConsole and IPMIConsole class

IPMISocatConsole is a new console interface class using ipmitool and
socat. It has the same APIs of IPMIShellinaboxConsole class and
provides TCP4/TCP6 connection service to connect serial-on-LAN of
nodes.
IPMIConsole is a new console interface class using ipmitool and used
as parent class of IPMIShellinaboxConsole and IPMISocatConsol class.

This patch set implements new console driver interfaces
IPMISocatConsole.

To use PXE + IPMItool + socat, specify pxe_ipmitool_socat.
To use IPA + IPMItool + socat, specify agent_ipmitool_socat.

Spec: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/319505/
Partial-Bug: #1553083
Change-Id: I35a7dcb7e89baf16d096501fd44dbc12adc8c61e

commit_message:
Fix l2_ml2_app bug

If l2_ml2_app is  used, when add_remote_port evnet is received, controller installs flow failed.
Because set(tunnel) does not support 'int' object.
This patch will fix this bug.

Change-Id: Idbccd61fa0ecffc6a283d8ed1671abbc07848ff6
Closes-bug: #1606854

commit_message:
Set up stable/newton temporary ACLs

Set up a temporary ACL rule for handling the upcoming
stable/newton release branches, for milestone-driven projects
which will go through a release candidate phase.

The $project-release-branch groups will have 'Release Managers'
as its initial member and admin. We'll add PTLs and release
liaisons to the groups pre-release, then add the stable maintenance
team at release time. Then the temporary ACLs will be removed.

This process lets us handle the transition from release branch to
stable branch gracefully and without too much sync points between
infra and release teams.

Change-Id: I16ab679ee7b1f9018299659ecdc03b089600f701

commit_message:
Swap neutron/nova-net multinode full jobs in nova check queue

This moves the neutron multinode job into nova's check queue
from experimental and the nova-net multinode job from check
to experimental. This is mostly because:

1. Nova broke the neutron multinode job, see:

   If515a90217a8e329d932dcacb357b78081c505c1

2. nova-network is deprecated.

3. The gate-tempest-dsvm-multinode-live-migration job in
   nova's check queue runs nova-net so we already have some
   coverage there for a multinode nova-net job (which is really
   what we have the multinode job for in the first place).

Change-Id: I25945171e8d489245690bbe8a68c9aff409d1e8b

commit_message:
Switch default partition type to gpt

Systems with >2TB 'disks' are becoming more commonplace on servers
with embedded raid arrays etc. Switch default partition type to gpt
from msdos when we find ourselves with a larger disk.

Co-Authored-By: Tom Hancock <tom.hancock@hp.com>

Change-Id: I9ab39ad7692df411a9a1c6998c0f701f9ee8e905
Closes-Bug: #1298362

commit_message:
Add functional tests for nested quotas

Adds functional tests for nested quotas as an alternative
to creating a Tempest test + gate job that would only run
Cinder related quota checks.

NOTE: The QUOTA engine in Cinder is a global variable that lazy loads
the quota driver, so even if we change the config for the quota driver,
we won't reliably change the driver being used (or change it back)
unless the global variables get cleaned up, so using mock instead of
overriding _get_flags to change the quota driver.

Co-Authored-By: Xinli Guan <xinli@us.ibm.com>

Change-Id: Ic9b7ef3c8e4978c1f1fee38a5c2511ba5cbe5559

commit_message:
Resolve unittest hang issue

This patch removes suspect decorator patch_no_sleep from VNX unit
test, and set the timeout = 0 when running tests to avoid potential
long running.

Also removed mock.patch of FixedIntervalLoopingCall from the setup
of Huawei unit test to prevent test_replication_driver_enable_success
in test_huawei_drivers.py from hanging.

Change-Id: I5c8efbf9a62e0f5bc39c5341b53f7af4e47c7e81
Partial-Bug: #1578986

subject: Remove array metadata when no items + fix case
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-07-29 18:42:08.000000000', 'files': ['horizon/static/framework/widgets/metadata/tree/tree.service.js', 'openstack_dashboard/static/app/core/metadata/modal/modal.controller.js', 'openstack_dashboard/static/app/core/metadata/modal/modal.controller.spec.js'], 'message': "Remove array metadata when no items + fix case

Array metadata appends an operator automatically, which
means the value will still contain something and it
doesn't get detected for removal.

In addition, bad APIs like glance v1 will store a property
with mixed case, but then return only lower case when
listing them. However, it will not remove the property
when you request to remove it unless it matches the original
case (sad panda).  So, this patch will reset the proper
casing for properties defined as metadata definitions before
making the request to save the metadata.

Change-Id: I1e5a6fde35b7be6118f21ac46ad0aea088280215
Closes-Bug: 1606988
"}]
commit_message:
Remove array metadata when no items + fix case

Array metadata appends an operator automatically, which
means the value will still contain something and it
doesn't get detected for removal.

In addition, bad APIs like glance v1 will store a property
with mixed case, but then return only lower case when
listing them. However, it will not remove the property
when you request to remove it unless it matches the original
case (sad panda).  So, this patch will reset the proper
casing for properties defined as metadata definitions before
making the request to save the metadata.

Change-Id: I1e5a6fde35b7be6118f21ac46ad0aea088280215
Closes-Bug: 1606988

commit_message:
Explicitly set heat.conf logging_exception_prefix

Gate logs for heat jobs really need to log stack traces with TRACE
instead of ERROR because some traces are being printed by passing
exc_info=True to LOG.info so they are not actual errors.

TRACE should be the default for oslo.log but something in the gate
setup is setting it to ERROR. Setting explicitly here restores the
desired pattern and protects against gate default overrides.

Change-Id: Id85287324fa6dc79d67fb1ed37c3f256d661133e
Closes-Bug: #1606404

commit_message:
Do not try to check for existing snapshots on Windows

There is no code to check for existing snapshots on Windows. Listing
them for that purpose just produces an error condition if the snapshot
does not exist (the common case) and the build aborts.

This patch removes the snapshot listing call from the Windows batch
files; it fixes a regression introduced with commit
3678ef2fa9893468604411ff697361bbd48d1e73.

Closes-Bug: #1606766
Change-Id: I221cabdf5e9948dda81cefdff7c8f3b3ab96817c

subject: Make shutdown command work on Windows
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-07-26 19:21:17.000000000', 'files': ['labs/osbash/lib/osbash/virtualbox-functions.sh'], 'message': 'Make shutdown command work on Windows

The recently introduced shutdown command did not make it into the
Windows batch files when calling osbash.sh only with the "-w" option
because in that case, vm_is_running would always return false.

This patch drops that check in vm_acpi_shutdown entirely. It is redundant
because every call to vm_acpi_shutdown is made from a location where the
VM is known to run (of course the VM can be stopped in the meantime,
but the removed check just made the window for that race somewhat
smaller without actually eliminating it).

Change-Id: Ia46705b2e9e78d9746a0c14685d724c53bfcdb47
'}]
commit_message:
Make shutdown command work on Windows

The recently introduced shutdown command did not make it into the
Windows batch files when calling osbash.sh only with the "-w" option
because in that case, vm_is_running would always return false.

This patch drops that check in vm_acpi_shutdown entirely. It is redundant
because every call to vm_acpi_shutdown is made from a location where the
VM is known to run (of course the VM can be stopped in the meantime,
but the removed check just made the window for that race somewhat
smaller without actually eliminating it).

Change-Id: Ia46705b2e9e78d9746a0c14685d724c53bfcdb47

commit_message:
Handle API NotFound exceptions at WSGI level

Throughout the API code we keep catching NotFound exceptions in their
various forms and converting them to webob.exc.HTTPNotFound exceptions,
but we can leave the WSGI fault handler convert them on its own.

This patch changes current behavior and removes the exception handling
closer to the operation so that those exceptions can be handled at the
WSGI level.

This has the following benefits:

- Reduces code complexity
- Increases code readability
- Provides consistent error responses, as messages are stored on the
  Exceptions.
- Prevents raising errors with only partial information (we have cases
  now that were removing the UUID from the message because they used a
  custom message).  For example: before returned error would be "The
  resource could not be found", and now we raise "Volume type encryption
  for type 4e9e6d23-eed0-426d-b90a-28f87a94b6fe does not exist."
  automatically.
- Reduces workload for the translation team because we remove all
  unnecessary custom messages.

Change-Id: I09f98921fdc2400cc3f6056e59001100abe06920

commit_message:
Add validate_db_int() method for validation

Added validate_db_int() method to check that given arguments
are of type int and should not exceed maximum value of SQL
integer type i.e., 2 ** 31 - 1.
Raise InputValidationError if argument is invalid.

Related-Bug: #1543937
Change-Id: I6f49bd2fdfe508cd7ff473a716860c4206221202

subject: Use assertEqual() instead of assertDictEqual()
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-07-27 06:26:32.000000000', 'files': ['senlin/tests/unit/profiles/test_nova_server.py'], 'message': "Use assertEqual() instead of assertDictEqual()

In unittesttools, assertDictEqual() and assertEqual()
are implemented by using '!=' operator. But assertEqual()
can handle dict, list, set and so on. So we just call
assertEqual() to make the tests simpler.

Change-Id: I165c7b408fec9afed399c4d0fcdd1bfebca5cd16
"}]
commit_message:
Use assertEqual() instead of assertDictEqual()

In unittesttools, assertDictEqual() and assertEqual()
are implemented by using '!=' operator. But assertEqual()
can handle dict, list, set and so on. So we just call
assertEqual() to make the tests simpler.

Change-Id: I165c7b408fec9afed399c4d0fcdd1bfebca5cd16

commit_message:
Add PostgreSQL models

Currently extensions/postgresql/service.py uses MySQL's models.
This commit creates PostgreSQL's model and use it.
By introducing PostgreSQL models, we can implement PostgreSQL specific
validation for character_set, password, etc.

Related-Bug: #1513150

commit_message:
ITRI DISCO cinder backup driver

This commit adds a Cinder backup driver for ITRI DISCO product.

The DISCO backup driver supports the following features:

* Backup any volume from any drivers to DISCO backend
* It will be incremental backup if it is a backup of a DISCO volume
* Restore a backup from DISCO storage system

It also includes the unit tests.

DocImpact
Implements: blueprint disco-backup-driver-cinder

Change-Id: Ifea020bb7b47a2d4ba179323a237c4a4d4510d12
